HEADWORD: Dysgenesis
<hw>Dys*gen"e*sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>dys-</ets> + <ets>genesis</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A
condition of not generating or breeding freely; infertility; a form of
homogenesis in which the hybrids are sterile among themselves, but are
fertile with members of either parent race.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

